---
import Article from '../layouts/Article.astro';

const title = 'Funscripts for The Handy - generate and play with FunGen';
const description =
  'Generate funscripts for The Handy from any 2D or VR video with FunGen, and play them over HTTPS or Bluetooth LE with latency compensation so they stay in sync.';
const canonicalPath = '/funscripts-for-the-handy';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');

const articleLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: 'Funscripts for The Handy with FunGen',
  description,
  inLanguage: 'en',
  dateModified: '2026-07-17',
  mainEntityOfPage: 'https://fungen.app/funscripts-for-the-handy',
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'FunGen' },
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'FunGen',
    logo: { '@type': 'ImageObject', url: 'https://fungen.app/icon-512.png' },
  },
};
const breadcrumbs = [{ name: 'The Handy', path: '/funscripts-for-the-handy' }];
---

<Article
  {title}
  {description}
  heading="Funscripts for The Handy"
  {canonicalPath}
  {articleLd}
  {breadcrumbs}
>
  <p class="lead">
    <a href={`${base}/`}>FunGen</a> both <strong>generates</strong> funscripts for The Handy and
    <strong>plays</strong> them straight to it - so you can take any 2D or VR video, script it with
    AI, and drive your Handy in sync, all from one app.
  </p>

  <h2>Generate a script for any video</h2>
  <p>
    The Handy reads a standard <a href={`${base}/what-is-a-funscript/`}>funscript</a> (the up/down
    stroke axis). Point FunGen at a clip - 2D, POV or VR - and a dedicated AI model writes that
    stroke track for you. Run a free 20-second preview first, then generate the full scene, or batch
    a whole folder. See <a href={`${base}/generate-funscripts-from-video/`}>the full how-to</a> for
    the steps.
  </p>

  <h2>Play to The Handy</h2>
  <p>FunGen connects to The Handy two ways:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>HTTPS (Handy Connect API)</strong> - drive it over the internet with your connection
      key, the most reliable path for streaming a script in time with the video.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Bluetooth LE</strong> - a direct local connection, no cloud round-trip, when your
      Handy and computer are in range.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Either way, FunGen applies <strong>per-device latency compensation</strong> so the motion lands
    on the beat rather than trailing the video - important for The Handy, where round-trip latency is
    real. You can fine-tune the offset if your setup needs it.
  </p>

  <h2>From the couch, the desk, or a headset</h2>
  <p>
    A built-in streamer lets you send the movie and its script to a phone, browser or VR headset
    while FunGen drives the Handy in sync - handy for VR scenes, where you watch in the headset and
    the device follows. The same script also works in players like HereSphere and DeoVR.
  </p>

  <h2>Make it feel right</h2>
  <p>
    The AI gets the motion; the editor makes it yours. Smooth or sharpen strokes, cap speed to what
    the Handy can comfortably hit, and run the <strong>Funscript Doctor</strong> - a device-aware
    quality score that flags speed violations and dead zones and fixes most of them in one click, so
    a script actually feels good on the hardware instead of just looking right on the timeline.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a href={`${base}/`}>Download FunGen</a> - free to try, runs on your own machine - and script your
    library for The Handy.
  </p>
</Article>
